[[!meta title="Howto add an Addon"]]

With `about:addons` you should be able to see but not install Firefox exenstions.

To install an extension you need to ensure the extension is correctly named as
it's install.rdf name and id, in the build configuration:

	x220:~/webc/Debian-Live-config/webconverger/config/includes.chroot/usr/lib/iceweasel/extensions$
	drwxrwxr-x 4 hendry users 4.0K Mar  4 13:28 touchkeyboard
	drwxrwxr-x 5 hendry users 4.0K Feb 17 15:06 webconverger
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 hendry users   12 Feb 17 15:02 {ee11fa88-036b-4661-bb04-d436f86bc06a} -> webconverger

Webconverger extension works, touchkeyboard doesn't.

	x220:~/webc/Debian-Live-config/webconverger/config/includes.chroot/usr/lib/iceweasel/extensions$
	grep name touchkeyboard/install.rdf
	<em:name>FxKeyboard</em:name>
	x220:~/webc/Debian-Live-config/webconverger/config/includes.chroot/usr/lib/iceweasel/extensions$
	mv touchkeyboard FxKeyboard

Lets correct the name.

	x220:~/webc/Debian-Live-config/webconverger/config/includes.chroot/usr/lib/iceweasel/extensions$
	grep id FxKeyboard/install.rdf
	<em:id>fxkeyboard@zabreznik.net</em:id>
	 <em:id>{ec8030f7-c20a-464f-9b0e-13a3a9e97384}</em:id>

`fxkeyboard@zabreznik.net` is this case is the id, however it's usually an UUID.

	x220:~/webc/Debian-Live-config/webconverger/config/includes.chroot/usr/lib/iceweasel/extensions$
	ln -s FxKeyboard fxkeyboard@zabreznik.net
	x220:~/webc/Debian-Live-config/webconverger/config/includes.chroot/usr/lib/iceweasel/extensions$
	ll
	total 16K
	drwxrwxr-x 4 hendry users 4.0K Mar  4 15:15 .
	drwxrwxr-x 3 hendry users 4.0K Feb 17 15:02 ..
	drwxrwxr-x 4 hendry users 4.0K Mar  4 13:28 FxKeyboard
	drwxrwxr-x 5 hendry users 4.0K Feb 17 15:06 webconverger
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 hendry users   12 Feb 17 15:02 {ee11fa88-036b-4661-bb04-d436f86bc06a} -> webconverger
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 hendry users   11 Mar  4 15:15 fxkeyboard@zabreznik.net -> FxKeyboard

Customised!
